Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Place two heaping tablespoons of parmesan cheese onto a non-stick cookie sheet and place in oven for 10 minutes. Dump tomato soup, milk, and tortellinis into a medium sauce pan and mix. Place on medium heat on stovetop burner for 10 minutes. Serve soup garnished with truffle oil floating on top and Parmesan Krisps on side!